       public final class ExternallyLinkedGroovyMethods {\n                /**\n                 * Converts {@code self} with values from {@link java.util.List}.\n                 *\n                 * @param self the receiver\n                 * @param values values from {@link java.util.List}\n                 * @return entries in a {@link java.util.Map}\n                 * @see java.util.Collections#emptyList()\n                 */\n                public static java.util.Map convert(java.lang.String self, java.util.List values) {\n                    return java.util.Collections.emptyMap();\n                }\n            }\n            '''.stripIndent())\n        return sourceFile\n    }\n\n    private List<Path> writeInheritedMethodSources() {\n"}]}
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating option parsing in CLI**\n\nI'm considering how the Apache Commons CLI handles the `valueSeparator`. Using `--link java.util=https://docs` neatly splits into two values. I also see that it can work with spaces: `--link java.util https://docs`. However, it seems that errors arise when the number of arguments is odd. I wonder if there’s a way to catch those errors and handle them for better user experience.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0a2b3f9cb1f1324b016a0033bab6bc8194bd9af31263b07db3\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqADPLyvO1DLE1KfYfNxlYyxnvIgmdH6XMRD-pxZfqmVst5Lu4N7EhmjyUrd-b0Aiq1E07YekI60A9Uv8K85JgFKrC1kmZLKlbhh2YIIuXuW9u5gTtxPybXW0KZlOhyTkmONpEFNRfeuYf3BWZZ5CxVF-RFfDbSjkn2q4JGCz3skQ25xRRWRbtbKh-egK7tATNbvjXp4USBt9oHuUOeLdcXrGwqObA2IaJwfm2GSvihD8_SgGjfu9-JHjR72sKp6-6vDTAfJUt9geexM56hcozgBmN8EKDMqIg37QVUopzqEHJjQuuLJIHp04P5SqFliU9gNA3D791xkf9a0UdOo82dqdUzOnaEmBBg561zRNps5swPywFed3uTRk5-zO2UzBmQZW5G2Hbhsq58KCS7IfmAh5rc41Wzu5DbIGRhjvCjzrG3HbxPwjtcxJEAqi2Kx3l1URqQEwIWpQZ1YIzPYyk61Rh9zLgd5ATyIvhXTF7wRs6YFMOnLYdz-uQoVGpRtVV5YhEVJqBPgpxHKzPOohIOiNcK64QRglhbYwzOltg7yRAQWxq99dpZLDhqVmR_QEs3l3hRyl48D0qDgCfw8Jsl1U4xjCRtwcZgrUsU60eU-NCkkXcWqq6KTP-g-3-zwcV0Xtfi8Z7E2vWecjT6VAkeTCoNPXL_a7cdxyuPqBHXEgHTPQhKHbx8p54IIAllGGRastiL3A8EiQBoR2drgtIfsvtv9fvL-I8Cc6IJjWdFodYdnOEWOiZWqCpaTXeoLjJRWQ_JiKeazIG-ofn-ZJIcpibyFhMYJiHoVmjodroXWVVjmVQHkIAj3vxI_4oe7Wp3vYW-0EIUvI9c6dWBxS6VQNA0lcIvDJGTBoEGPLO8ZBU6GzYIGBnEYF0Jt0FKbiE8GvWhiK5LL3ejTuB4EYG8hNgOOJLtr84CuFqJfiiAZyCr-A-GkD8M8YEMx1vX1-lzQfU_JBGu2V32zx-dBOWEn3yK1Z1qnlRBwreYsXyA-8Ukht4vaoG-SVnPfOwqKahTYdY1em5QkWiJYDNv9qjc7oVKeIIQ-LX6da6T2xW3pFxJLVjeXvVRQfveFXO75qvK1JTpeTodJZnFJy_ho8tN0c5DQSzYr-cDDmV-kDMwRxf-Y6Gb96eyCUvnIhhLfj-5iCdZ6l28GlirY5Y7hWHzG2zyWkbT5VdYfmt5DcTj_ccrxekxFK3dkjqBy5y0_82_Lmf84QLvggodGmLMspcfSDM_1baDyjldROC4UL88v2ItaJgQ2N9w932ELdp0r557u3xUDamFsdOQOcDxL6N4iQgu7MuB1qf6AhpZMgiSX8b